The paper presents a new framework for online learning that extends the existing Passive-Aggressive (PA) learning algorithm to incorporate Bayesian inference and nonparametric methods. This makes it applicable to a wide range of explorative analysis tasks, including topic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
